data.title: Andrii Dushkevych - Software Engineer at KUBRA
data.meta_description:
Andrii Dushkevych's work experience includes:

- Software Engineer at KUBRA since February 2023.
data.text:
Andrii Dushkevych's work experience includes:

- Software Engineer at KUBRA since February 2023.

- Software Developer at Appara from December 2021 to February 2023. Duties included designing, implementing, and testing features for a document automation platform using C#, Entity Framework, Bridge.NET, and React. Additionally, designed and implemented scripts and workflows for Azure DevOps CI/CD pipelines.

- Software Developer at GEOTAB from April 2021 to December 2021. Responsibilities included implementing backend logic for fleet management software using .NET Core Web API and Postgres database, as well as working with TypeScript on UI components.

- Software Developer at LogiSense Corporation from May 2019 to April 2021. Developed new features for a usage-based rating/billing ASP.Net web application and designed and developed MSSQL database stored procedures and queries.

- Freelance Software Developer, self-employed, from 2017 to 2019. Tasks included designing and developing ASP.Net web applications for various clients and implementing UI/UX designed pages using HTML, CSS, and Bootstrap.

- Junior Software Developer at Terrasoft from October 2016 to July 2017. Implemented new features for an ASP.Net CRM application with MSSQL database and developed UI modules using JavaScript.

Andrii Dushkevych's education history includes:

- From 2017 to 2019, they attended Conestoga College where they studied Software Engineering.

- From 2013 to 2017, they attended the National Technical University of Ukraine 'Kyiv Polytechnic Institute' and earned a Bachelor's degree in Computer and Information Systems Security/Information Assurance.

In addition to their formal education, Andrii has obtained several certifications:

- In June 2023, they completed the "Developing on AWS" certification from Amazon Web Services (AWS).

- In March 2021, they completed the "Azure Administration Essential Training" certification from LinkedIn.

- Also in March 2021, they completed the "Microservices Foundations" certification from LinkedIn.

- In the same month of March 2021, they completed the "Practical Application Architecture with Entity Framework Core" certification from LinkedIn.

- In November 2020, they obtained the "Verified International Academic Qualifications" certification from World Education Services.

- In August 2019, they completed the "Build an app with ASP.NET Core and Angular from scratch" certification from Udemy.

- In November 2016, they obtained the "Разработка на платформе bpm’online" certification from bpm'online.

It is also noted that Andrii has a certification titled "Blazor WebAssembly in .NET 6" from Udemy, but specific information regarding the month and year of its completion is not provided.
